  {:id :sorry/r3d-per-entity-attribution
   :title "R3d wiring uses crude global attribution; refine to per-entity once real per-entity event streams arrive"
   :raised-at "2026-05-18"
   :status :open
   :kind :prototyping-forward
   :predecessor-satisfied-at "2026-05-26"
   :predecessor-satisfied-by "M-INC step (b) committed by claude-3 as futon3/library/structure/interest-event-vocabulary.flexiarg; the typed event vocabulary that was the named prerequisite for per-entity attribution now exists on disk.  Re-typing this sorry from :campaign-scale (its earlier classification in M-action-cost-modelling §3.2) to :mission-scale follows.  Still :open at the implementation level — the R3d rewiring to consume per-entity events hasn't yet landed — but the architectural blocker is gone."
   :partial-closure-notes
   "v0.16 (2026-05-19) addressed the MULTI-CHANNEL limitation of this
    sorry: judge's R3 inner-loop now aggregates signed weighted-errors
    across all 4 R3a-covered channels (using channel-health-signs in
    preferences) rather than driving from :annotation-health alone.
    What REMAINS open: the same aggregated event is still applied
    UNIFORMLY to every entity in the belief domain. Per-entity
    attribution awaits real per-entity event streams (M-INC step (b))."
   :rationale
   (str
    "v0.10 R3d wiring in `futon2.report.war-machine/judge` synthesises a "
    "single global belief-update event from the :annotation-health "
    "prediction-error and applies it uniformly to every entity in the "
    "belief domain (positive error → :strengthened on all entities; "
    "negative → :foreclosed on all entities; weight = min(1, |weighted-error|) * 0.1). "
    "This is honest as a v1 placeholder — it lets :mu-post ≠ :mu-pre on "
    "every call so the bilateral comparison with VSATARCS-side can "
    "witness drift — but it is NOT honest as per-entity Bayesian update: "
    "the aggregate signal can't legitimately be attributed equally to "
    "every entity. "
    "\n\n"
    "Refinement path: when real per-entity event streams arrive (M-INC "
    "step (b), or a substrate adapter that surfaces per-entity state "
    "changes), the global synthetic event gets replaced by per-entity "
    "events that carry the attribution honestly. Until then, the v0.10 "
    "wiring stays — it's a prototype that lets downstream components "
    "(trace, bilateral bridge, R9 properties) be exercised against real "
    "non-zero belief evolution. "
    "\n\n"
    "Classified as :prototyping-forward (per Joe 2026-05-18): we knew "
    "the v0.10 shape was incomplete when we shipped it, but the "
    "refinement IS the work — not technical debt accrued from cutting "
    "corners. The distinction matters because the WM's intrinsic-value "
    "credit on :address-sorry actions could eventually be tuned by "
    ":kind, recognising that :prototyping-forward sorries are progress "
    "indicators rather than failure indicators.")
   :related-missions ["M-war-machine-aif-completion"
                      "M-stack-essay-code-alignment"
                      "M-interest-network-coupling"]
   :links ["futon2/docs/futon-aif-completeness.md#r3-predictive-coding-belief-update"
           "futon2/scripts/futon2/report/war_machine.clj"]}

