  {:id :sorry/wm-ui-hud-mode-rationale-hardcode
   :title "WM UI HUD Mode tooltip rationale is hardcoded; should be sourced dynamically from strategic-vocabulary :μ/modes"
   :raised-at "2026-05-24"
   :status :open
   :kind :prototyping-forward
   :rationale
   (str
    "Anchor 0004 of `~/code/futon5a/data/wm-ui-anchors.edn` discharged "
    "2026-05-24 via a v1 tooltip on the HUD Mode span "
    "(`futon2/web/war-machine/src/war_machine/client/hud.cljs`). The per-mode "
    "rationale text is hardcoded as a small map (`mode-rationale`) at the top "
    "of `hud.cljs`, sourced from `war-machine-strategic-vocabulary.edn` "
    "`:μ/modes` lines 147-159 (the 6-mode taxonomy with one-line "
    "rationales per mode).\n\n"
    "v1 hardcode is the right call because vocab changes are rare and "
    "dynamic EDN read is substrate-side work that wasn't in the anchor-0004 "
    "scope. But the duplication is real: if the vocab updates its "
    "mode-rationale prose, the hud.cljs map has to re-sync manually. "
    "Drift surface is small but tracked.\n\n"
    "Resolution path (either-or): (a) dynamic vocab read — have the WM "
    "UI fetch the vocab EDN at boot and parse it client-side; (b) "
    "vocab-to-cljs codegen on substrate-side build — a small `bb` script "
    "generates the `mode-rationale` map from the vocab during the shadow-cljs "
    "release pipeline. (b) keeps the runtime free of EDN parsing; (a) keeps "
    "the build pipeline simple. Pick at v2 when at least one of the other "
    "HUD anchors (0001/0003/0005/0006/0007) hits the same hardcode "
    "pattern and the duplication compounds.\n\n"
    "Authored co-located with the anchor-0004 landing per claude-10's "
    "M-war-machine-vsatarcs-interop bell-protocol point #2 (2026-05-24).")
