  {:id :sorry/mission-aif-head-not-served
   :title "Mission-AIF head computes locally but is not yet a typed surface readable by the WM head"
   :raised-at "2026-05-27"
   :status :addressed
   :kind :prototyping-forward
   :resolved-at "2026-05-29"
   :resolved-by-cg "cg-a4eaabf8-c0a1-4b07-b295-c73e5d683365"
   :resolved-by-pilot "claude-2"
   :resolution
   (str
    "Addressed via bridge candidate (c): the WM head now READS the mission-AIF "
    "head's local computation in-process. Root cause first: futon3c.aif.mission-head "
    "was dead code in the serving JVM — its dep futon3c.aif.invariant threw an "
    "ArityException (a docstring passed to defonce) and never loaded, so the head "
    "did not actually 'compute locally' at all. Fixed that defonce; the head now "
    "computes locally for real. scan-aif-heads (futon2 war_machine.clj) un-stubbed "
    "to surface the head's reading → mission-aif-head :available? true, missing-count "
    "0. The head is now a typed surface readable by the WM head — the literal gap "
    "this sorry named.\n\n"
    "Scope: bridge (c) done; richer forms remain available if a future mission needs "
    "them — (a) per-mission mission/v01/aif-snapshot hyperedge, (b) substrate-2 "
    "anamnesis T-projection. Discharged through the differential-operator REPL "
    "(futon3c/holes/specs/repl.spec.edn) as the first substantive live cycle; fork "
    "resolved via §8 fork-resolution (pattern warrant → A).")
   :rationale
   (str
    "M-action-cost-modelling §3.8 (aliveness synthesis) and the R5 EFE "
    "augmentation establish a Mission-AIF head — a per-mission scoring "
    "surface combining G-risk + G-amb − 0.4·G-info + 1.2·G-survival over "
    "anamnesis-bearing artifacts. The head computes locally during mission "
    "lifecycle phases (codex-5 + claude-1 cycle 2026-05-26/27) but its "
    "outputs are not yet a queryable substrate-2 surface.\n\n"
    "Consequence: the WM head (`/api/alpha/war-machine/ranked-actions`) "
    "cannot consume mission-AIF deltas as evidence in its own scoring; "
    "the two AIF surfaces live on different timescales without a typed "
    "bridge. The aliveness synthesis is one quantity; the surfaces should "
    "be projections of it, not unrelated heads.\n\n"
    "Bridge candidates: (a) per-mission AIF snapshot as a "
    "`mission/v01/aif-snapshot` hyperedge written at phase exits; (b) "
    "anamnesis-region T-projection on substrate-2 (this is what "
    "E-substrate-2-sorry-typing partially supplies for sorry-anamnesis "
    "only); (c) WM head reads mission-AIF as a peripheral evidence-kind "
    "rather than a substrate read. Pick at next mission-spawn that needs "
    "cross-head reasoning — likely the M-action-cost-modelling INSTANTIATE "
    "phase or a sibling mission that explicitly consumes mission-aliveness "
    "as input.")
