  {:id :sorry/handler-closure-route-rebinding
   :title "Handler closures captured at server-start time don't see hot-swapped vars after Drawbridge :reload"
   :raised-at "2026-05-27"
   :status :addressed
   :resolved-at "2026-05-30"
   :resolved-by-cg "cg-6965e5e6-ba14-4a6b-8690-bbf29bbd2a38"
   :resolved-by-pilot "claude-5 (war-machine-pilot, run live-00c07332)"
   :resolution
   (str
    "Resolution candidates (a)+(c) executed — the pairing the sorry's own "
    "text named as cheapest. AUDIT (a): the futon3c serving path dispatches "
    "via DIRECT SYMBOL CALLS inside fn bodies — `make-handler`'s cond "
    "(`(handle-dispatch request config)`), the watcher "
    "(`(file-ingest/dispatch! ...)`), the scheduler's recurring Runnable "
    "(`(fn [] (tick!))`, scheduler.clj:265). A bare top-level symbol in a fn "
    "body compiles to a CALL-TIME var dereference, so handler BODIES are "
    "reload-safe by construction; the `(#'var ...)` idiom is redundant there. "
    "The genuine stale-closure hazard is narrower than the original framing: "
    "it bites only when a fn is CAPTURED AS A VALUE (stored in a dispatch "
    "map, registered once as a callback, or closed over by a thread started "
    "once). No such site exists in the current request path. The one "
    "non-reload-safe case is ROUTE-TABLE STRUCTURE change (adding a cond "
    "branch), which needs a handler re-wire — distinct from var hot-swap. "
    "DOC (c): documented the full taxonomy in README-drawbridge.md "
    "(section 'Reload-safety: what a reload picks up, and what it doesn''t'), "
    "replacing the prior imprecise note that claimed reloads don't refresh "
    "handlers at all. (b) the `defhandler` macro is NOT needed — there is no "
    "data-driven route map to protect. Reload-safety = reconstructibility "
    "from disk per feedback_reload_safety; this gap is now closed as scoped.")
   :kind :prototyping-forward
   :rationale
   (str
    "Observed during the rapid review-code cycle for "
    "E-substrate-2-sorry-typing (codex-5 INSTANTIATE 2026-05-27): when a "
    "watcher-integrated ingest path is added by editing "
    "`futon3c/src/futon3c/watcher/file_ingest.clj` and reloaded via "
    "Drawbridge nREPL, the route handlers in the running JVM may still "
    "hold closures over the prior var values. The route table dispatch "
    "is correct, but the captured handler function is the pre-reload "
    "one.\n\n"
    "Workaround currently in use: handler bodies that do `(#'ns/var "
    "args)` instead of `(ns/var args)` so the var is re-resolved at "
    "each call. This is the standard idiom but it's not consistently "
    "applied across the futon3c route layer; some handlers were authored "
    "before the Drawbridge-reload pattern was canonical.\n\n"
    "Resolution candidates: (a) audit pass on "
    "`futon3c/src/futon3c/server.clj` and the handler-registration sites "
    "to ensure all production handlers go through the `#'var` indirection; "
    "(b) helper macro `defhandler` that emits the indirection automatically; "
    "(c) document the discipline in `README-drawbridge.md` so new handlers "
    "are authored correctly from the start. (c) is the cheapest and "
    "should be paired with (a) on the next route-layer touch. "
    "Reload-safety = reconstructibility from disk per "
    "feedback_reload_safety; this sorry tracks the partial gap.")
   :related-missions ["M-drawbridge-multi-agent"]
   :links ["~/code/futon3c/src/futon3c/transport/http.clj"
           "~/code/futon3c/src/futon3c/wm/scheduler.clj"
           "~/code/futon3c/README-drawbridge.md"]}]}
